der philosophy or psychoanalysis. As this work demonstrates, the image of the nursing divine is intended to cultivate a direct emotional response to God rooted in nurture, love, and reliance, rather than knowledge, sexuality, or authority.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aCabalaxHistory. 0aGod (Judaism)xLove. 0aMysticismxJudaism. 0aRabbinical literaturexHistory and criticism. 4aJewish Studies : Jewish Studies. 7aRELIGION / Judaism / Kabbalah & Mysticism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438443829423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438443829/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles